entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things you really like about la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the weather is great i love being near the ocean and the palm trees and mountains i just love it here

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy was it for you to get used to living in la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was pretty easy there is a few differences it is a huge city compared to where i am from so traffic has definitely been an adjustment for me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why would you move to la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i just always wanted to live in california hated being landlocked in oklahoma just wanted to get out to the west coast be near the ocean

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what would you study at school

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i studied psychology and minored in art

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are you still working in that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no not at the moment

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: to relax i like to read or watch movies i like to go to the beach and just watch the sunset or hang out with friends

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: things that make me really mad probably injustice towards other people people being mistreated or abused and people being lied to and deceived including myself i hate being lied to

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: when i am annoyed depends on the situation but i try to just like count to ten and take a deep breath and and not let my emotions cause me to react in a negative way so i just try and like calm down before i say anything

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it depends again on the situation and like who i am angry with most of the time i am pretty good at controlling it but sometimes i think like like most people i will lash out at the people that i am closest to at times and and those moments i am not that good at controlling it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: when was the last time i argued with someone it was probably with my parents i have been having some some car trouble lately and i am also running low on money so i am sure i do not even remember exactly but i am sure we kind of probably fought about the fact that i you know need to be more self sufficient and independent take care of my own things like car issues

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how close are you to your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am very close with my family they are still in oklahoma but i talk to them on the phone all the time

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is one of your most memorable experiences

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh probably the time i went bungee jping over the nile river in uganda i still kinda have flashbacks of that moment just freefalling it was like the coolest experience ever and i love doing things that are crazy like that so it was a fun time

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you travel a lot

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah well i have i have traveled a lot nowadays i do not travel so much anymore but i used to work for a cruise line norwegian cruise line and so i would go travel all the time with them and then i also did an eleven month long trip around the world it was a mission trip so i just went and helped out in different third world countries it was really cool

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you enjoy about traveling

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i just love going to different places seeing new places and meeting all different types of people because it is easy to just like get so absorbed in your own small bubble that you forget that there is a huge world out there and there is all different types of people with all different types of beliefs and it is just really cool to be able to branch out and see and meet those types of people and see just the diversity and the terrain of the earth even and the way that the earth looks in different places is cool

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever served in the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not served in the military

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: nope

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have never been formally diagnosed although i would say i have probably diagnosed myself with depression just after having studied it a lot in psychology throughout the years i have i am probably ninety nine percent sure that i have struggled with depression off and on so yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: lately it is been pretty easy but throughout the years i have definitely had a lot of issues with insomnia just like either not being able to fall asleep or just like waking up constantly throughout the night and so right now i am not really experiencing too much of that but in the past it is definitely been an ongoing issue for me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am not a pleasant person when i do not sleep well sleep is extremely like important for me i think maybe more so than a lot of people i i like need good sleep to function

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have been feeling really good over the past several months i was unemployed after coming out here and that was really really tough and i just recently got offered my job just like last week so i definitely think i have been going through a lot of crap and just a lot of depression but it is like lifted a lot of it has been lifted off me because i do not have that pressure any longer of like how am i gonna make ends meet this city is really expensive and i do not have a job and so i feel i feel much more relieved than i have been feeling which is good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah well i mean just like i said over the past week or so i have become a lot more positive i was kind of like feeling a bit like a hermit in a way it is just hard like being in a new city and not really knowing too many people and of course like i said not having a job kind of causes you to kind of just like be in your own shell i guess and that was kinda how it was how it is been for me and just since i got offered the job i just have so much more confidence and like positivity that things are are starting to work out for me which is good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh it was probably a couple of days ago actually i went i went to explore a part of the south bay area that i had not really been to before and it was i was just gonna go for a jog along the beach and it was really foggy outside and then the fog started to lift and it was just beautiful and then i i went for a drive up off kind of off this like cliff where there is beautiful scenery that i would never seen before and i just like was overwhelmed with how pretty it was and i was just like oh i can not believe that i get to live here so that was definitely a happy moment for me
